German Pharmacies to Watch for Cheap Imports, Sueddeutsche Says

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-08-22T06:56:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/german-pharmacies-to-watch-for-cheap-imports-sueddeutsche-says.html
German pharmacies are being asked by
IMS Health, a research firm, to notify it of cheap medicine
imports, also known as parallel imports,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung 
reported today, citing IMS documents.  IMS is offering pharmacies digital cameras to photograph
the imports and will pay them for photographs and packaging
information, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 